unacknowledged in the novel.

00:23:25.670 --> 00:23:30.450
The mystery of Cintra
Road, published in 1870,

00:23:30.450 --> 00:23:32.990
is considered the first
detective story written

00:23:32.990 --> 00:23:34.910
in the Portuguese language,

00:23:34.910 --> 00:23:39.900
by Portugal's most famed 19th
century author, Eca de Queiros,

00:23:39.900 --> 00:23:43.150
and his friend, Ramalho Ortigao.

00:23:43.150 --> 00:23:47.180
The mystery of Cintra Road
was a satirical literary hoax

00:23:47.180 --> 00:23:50.680
about the supposed accidental
murder of a young Englishman

00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:53.150
by his beautiful Portuguese lover.

00:23:53.150 --> 00:23:55.800
Delivered in a series
of letters to the editor

00:23:55.800 --> 00:23:58.740
of the Lisbon newspaper,
Diario Di Noticias.

00:23:58.740 --> 00:24:02.640
And this is an image of
the first, the first one.

00:24:02.640 --> 00:24:06.270
The final letter spread
over more than two months.

00:24:06.270 --> 00:24:10.140 position:56%
In the final letter, the two authors
revealed that the case is not news

00:24:10.140 --> 00:24:13.770
of a real murder at all,
but a literary fiction.

00:24:15.110 --> 00:24:18.750
The key to figuring
out the hoax is style.

00:24:18.750 --> 00:24:21.000
The two authors said
they wrote it to make fun

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:24.480
of a Portuguese reading public
that they see as uncritical

00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:28.830
of the exaggerated and tired
tropes of the sentimentalist novels

00:24:28.830 --> 00:24:31.400
that were popular in
Portugal at the time.

00:24:31.400 --> 00:24:33.580
But which the two writers
saw as markers

00:24:33.580 --> 00:24:37.900
of Portugal's backwards tastes
and lack of sophistication.

00:24:37.900 --> 00:24:42.050 position:56%
The clue to figuring out the prank
lies in contrasting it with the new,

00:24:42.050 --> 00:24:45.080
modern style epitomized
in modern French poets

00:24:45.080 --> 00:24:47.890
and writers like Edgar Allen Poe.

00:24:47.890 --> 00:24:52.090 position:56%
Both modern style and sentimentalist
tropes are evident when one

00:24:52.090 --> 00:24:55.100
of the main characters it
finds a clue to the murder.

00:24:55.100 --> 00:25:00.090
A single hair that turns out to
belong to the murderer herself.

00:25:00.090 --> 00:25:01.390
Quote.

00:25:01.390 --> 00:25:04.690
The person to whom it
belonged was blond, fair.

00:25:04.690 --> 00:25:05.990
Certainly small.

00:25:05.990 --> 00:25:09.270
Mignon. Because the strand
of hair was very fine.

00:25:09.270 --> 00:25:11.120
Extremely pure.

00:25:11.120 --> 00:25:15.850 position:56%
The character of this person must be
sweet, humble, dedicated and loving.

00:25:15.850 --> 00:25:17.780
She must have simple tastes.

00:25:17.780 --> 00:25:20.540
Elegantly modest, the
owner of this hair.

00:25:20.540 --> 00:25:23.800
She was likely educated in
England or Germany, because the tip

00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:27.360
of the hair was cut into a point,
a habit of the women of the North,

00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:31.060 position:56%
