women, who abandoned their locks

00:25:31.060 --> 00:25:33.070
to their abundant natural
coarseness.

00:25:33.070 --> 00:25:34.370
End quote.

00:25:34.370 --> 00:25:38.600
The narrator's careful
examination of the hair results

00:25:38.600 --> 00:25:42.400
in all the stereotypes of
the sentimentalist heroine.

00:25:42.400 --> 00:25:44.430
Although the narrator here is able

00:25:44.430 --> 00:25:46.860
to glean a comically
excessive amount of detail

00:25:46.860 --> 00:25:52.240 position:56%
from a single object, another
sentimentalist trope gets in the way

00:25:52.240 --> 00:25:55.050
of satisfactorily resolving
the crime.

00:25:55.050 --> 00:25:58.360
All the five young men determined
to figure out what happened

00:25:58.360 --> 00:26:01.600
to their friend fall in
love with the murderer.

00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:04.340
And thus, they end up helping her
get rid of the body and retire

00:26:04.340 --> 00:26:07.700
to a convent, rather
than face justice.

00:26:07.700 --> 00:26:12.690
These two elements, the unresolved
crime and the satire of style,

00:26:12.690 --> 00:26:16.990
are what I'm calling on to link
the 19th century Portuguese text

00:26:16.990 --> 00:26:19.710
with the 21st century Angolan one.

00:26:19.710 --> 00:26:23.230
Especially through the
notion of counterfeiting.

00:26:23.230 --> 00:26:25.730
The counterfeit news
that the Mystery

00:26:25.730 --> 00:26:29.580
of Cinta Street represents
reappears in Jaime Bunda,

00:26:29.580 --> 00:26:34.370
Secret Agent as a false conspiracy
that Jaime conceives in order

00:26:34.370 --> 00:26:36.470
to deliver some results
to his bosses

00:26:36.470 --> 00:26:39.200 position:56%
when he fails at solving the murder.

00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:43.560
He stages a raid on a made-up
drug ring, but to his surprise,

00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:46.900
discovers in the process actual
criminals, who are scheming

00:26:46.900 --> 00:26:51.820
to exchange counterfeit
Angolan kwanzas for US dollars.

00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:53.340
You're a genius, Shinito.

00:26:53.340 --> 00:26:55.880
You're go far in the service,
his partner tells him,

00:26:55.880 --> 00:26:58.630
after Jaime reveals the plot.

00:26:58.630 --> 00:27:03.140 position:56%
Jaime's genius, and his invention of
stories, differs only in the details

00:27:03.140 --> 00:27:05.360
from the crime he actually
discovers.

00:27:05.360 --> 00:27:08.750
The narrative structure
is more or less the same.

00:27:08.750 --> 00:27:11.640
On the one hand, this
conclusion certainly points

00:27:11.640 --> 00:27:15.640
to Pepetela's critique of
corrupt public officials.

00:27:15.640 --> 00:27:18.830
Jaime invents a story
that brings him success,

00:27:18.830 --> 00:27:22.280
but the social milieu is so
replete with crimes that he ends

00:27:22.280 --> 00:27:25.970 position:56%
