00:27:45.450 --> 00:27:48.340
I think that this mapping
together of the acknowledged

00:27:48.340 --> 00:27:51.910
and unacknowledged sources
are crucial to the novel.

00:27:51.910 --> 00:27:55.540 position:56%
For the Portuguese novel, the
detective formula serves as a marker

00:27:55.540 --> 00:27:59.570
of literary modernity that guides
the astute reader to figure

00:27:59.570 --> 00:28:02.300
out the hoax and the tricks
the uninformed reader,

00:28:02.300 --> 00:28:04.880
who fails to perceive the clues.

00:28:04.880 --> 00:28:07.730
In the Angolan novel, the
history of the crime genre,

00:28:07.730 --> 00:28:12.570 position:56%
referenced through-out the text,
has itself become the formulaic form

00:28:12.570 --> 00:28:15.800
and style that is ultimately
insufficient.

00:28:15.800 --> 00:28:19.090
At least as deployed
through Jaime Bunda's lens,

00:28:19.090 --> 00:28:20.430
to grasp the complexity

00:28:20.430 --> 00:28:23.790
of the Angolan society
in which it operates.

00:28:23.790 --> 00:28:27.650
In most crime fiction, the
reader is also the detective.

00:28:27.650 --> 00:28:31.450
And the economy of the text
provides the necessary clues

00:28:31.450 --> 00:28:35.360
for both the detective and the
reader to follow the logic.

00:28:35.360 --> 00:28:40.380
While Jaime can apply the narrative
formula to his Luandan context,

00:28:40.380 --> 00:28:45.160
the intimate integration of the
content and the style fall apart.

00:28:45.160 --> 00:28:48.360
The layering of the two
English and Portuguese sources

00:28:48.360 --> 00:28:53.160
of literary styles operates as
both a critique and a warning.

00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:58.270 position:56%
If the revolution sought to cast off
the vestiges of colonial occupation,

00:28:58.270 --> 00:29:00.720
replacing Portuguese
political hegemony

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:04.750
with American cultural hegemony
leaves the fundamental colonial

00:29:04.750 --> 00:29:07.000
formulas intact.

00:29:07.000 --> 00:29:10.850
The old and the new colonial
regimes float just above

00:29:10.850 --> 00:29:14.380
and just below the
surface of Angolan reality.

00:29:14.380 --> 00:29:17.500
For Pepetela and for
Jaime Bunda's world,

00:29:17.500 --> 00:29:21.810
